External knowledge:
- "effect strength" refers to the magnitude of the effect of an item, which in this case is multiplied by 100 to be combined with the total transaction value;
- "combined value" is a calculated value that represents the total value of an item, including its transaction value and effect strength.

External knowledge: 
The frequency of transactions for each item is determined by the count of transaction_id for each item_id; 
The item types include 'Weapon', 'Armor', etc.;
The top 3 items for each type are those with the highest transaction counts.
